“Everyone has heard that gas prices continue to rise,” read an email that came from the account of Wayne Pankratz, executive director of operations for Applebee’s franchisee Apple Central LLC. “The advantage this has for us is that it will increase application flow and has the potential to lower our average wage. How you ask?

“Most of our employee base and potential employee base live paycheck to paycheck. Any increase in gas price cuts into their disposable income. As inflation continues to climb and gas prices continue to go up, that means more hours employees will need to work to maintain their current level of living.” 

Evil sauce: https://www2.ljworld.com/news/general-news/2022/mar/23/an-email-urging-lower-wages-for-new-employees-due-to-higher-gas-prices-sparks-walkout-at-lawrence-applebees/?utm_source=fark&utm_medium=website&utm_c</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/bEEN4mB</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[HorrorMango]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>So... My Parents Turned Racist</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/16oc0GN</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/i2FoAEi.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I moved my family back to my rural home town after being away for years. It's the most isolating depressing experience of my entire life. After seeing other Christians embrace Trump and other forms of hate, and experiencing absolutely no indication of God being a reality for me personally, I finally became atheist/agnostic. 

In this town, I've been called names by friends and family for masking up, even as friends and family died from the Coronavirus. 

Now Idaho, asking with other states, just passed cruel, extreme abortion laws. I was talking with my 75 year old mom about it and realized she was in support of teenage girls being forced to bare children when they are molested or raped.

It was a heated conversation so this morning I tried to patch things up a bit, but in the conversation my mom started taking about liberal oppressors and actually said "Black people are trying to take away our freedom". 

When I asked her how black people are being oppressed she couldn't explain how other than saying Roseanne Barr had been fired.

She didn't use to be like this entirely but has fallen deep down the conspiracy hole. She's not much of a thinker on her own and I'm sure she got these ideas from my dad. My family and everybody I know in this community is the same.

I was just keeping quite and trying not to talk with them at all, but as I see fascism sweeping the country, I'm realizing that if I'm going to make a stand, it has to be now. I have to ask people around me the tough questions.

After trying a number of techniques, I'm realizing Street Epistemology - asking questions with as little judgement possible - is about the only way to break through people's ideologies. When they start to hear their own voice contradict themselves, cracks in their dogma start to open up.

I had often wondered how the Christian Germans supported the cruel Nazi movement. Now I realize they gave up all morality for religious zeal. 

Ironically, I feel like a missionary of sorts. If liberals and moderates are to make any headway, we need spread into the rural areas where our vote can not be divided out easily. 

I'm so tired and alone though. I can't believe how ignorant people are about history, about the people and ideas they support. So pious, arrogant and sure in their idiocracy.

And fear of "the end" is sweeping everyone, liberal and conservative. I wonder if it's genetic memory - at least 7 times the dominant species had been wired out here on Earth.

